<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Death-bed" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Death-bed,</orth> the bed in which a person dies: <bibl n="shak. son 73.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 73, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.164" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 193</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 51</bibl>. Evans says: <cit><quote>upon his death's bed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 53</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>